description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Programme Support Officer in Public Health&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:  £20,206 to £23,226 p.a.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Public Health Team at Swindon Borough Council is seeking to recruit an experienced and motivated individual to provide administrative support to the public health team. This role is a full time, permanent role but part time hours will be considered for the right candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to create healthy, strong and resilient communities. Our highly successful public health team works to improve and protect the health of Swindon residents, tackle health inequalities and protect the most vulnerable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be an experienced administrator with good communication and organisational skills who is able to work flexibly in a busy environment as part of a team and independently.   If you enjoy working a fast-paced environment you will be rewarded by the diversity of the role, whilst developing your own public health career within a passionate team, we would very much like to hear from you.  The applicant must be experienced in use of MS Office including Microsoft Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is home-based working at the present time but with a requirement to be able to travel to Swindon Borough Council Offices, Central Swindon and across the Borough as required. Swindon Borough Council terms and conditions apply to this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be fluent in the English language (as a requirement of Part 7 of the Immigration Act – for the effective performance of a customer-facing role).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the role, before applying, please contact Moira Shields by email at MShields@Swindon.gov.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 22 November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 30 November 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
